{% extends "common/layout.njk" %}

{% set pageTitle = 'Getting started' %}
{% set page = 'getting-started' %}

{% block content %}
  <div class="govuk-width-container govuk-!-margin-top-6 govuk-!-margin-bottom-8">

    <div class="govuk-grid-row">
      <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">

        <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Getting started</h1>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Using this registry with GitHub Copilot</h2>

        <p class="govuk-body">
          GitHub Copilot supports MCP server allowlist enforcement at the organisation level.
          An organisation administrator can set a registry URL in their Copilot policy settings.
          When the policy is set to <strong>Registry only</strong>, Copilot checks each configured
          MCP server against the registry and flags any server whose ID is not listed.
          See the
          <a class="govuk-link" href="https://docs.github.com/en/copilot/reference/mcp-allowlist-enforcement" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">GitHub Copilot MCP allowlist enforcement documentation</a>
          for full details.
        </p>

        <p class="govuk-body">
          Defra runs two GitHub organisations for Copilot — one for wider production use and one
          for testing and evaluation. Each organisation's registry URL is pointed at a different
          channel of this registry:
        </p>

        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>
            <strong>Production organisation</strong> — registry URL set to the
            <strong class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--blue">Stable</strong> channel
            (<code>/registry/stable/v0.1/servers</code>), which returns only fully approved servers.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Testing organisation</strong> — registry URL set to the
            <strong class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--yellow">Canary</strong> channel
            (<code>/registry/canary/v0.1/servers</code>), which includes all stable servers plus
            those currently under evaluation.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Adding a server to the registry</h2>

        <p class="govuk-body">
          All servers go through a two-stage process before becoming available to all Defra teams.
        </p>

        <ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
          <li>
            <strong>Canary.</strong> New servers are added to the Canary channel first. At this
            stage they are available only to designated pilot teams. The AICE team evaluates
            the server against Defra's security, licensing and supportability criteria.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Stable.</strong> Once evaluation is complete and the server is approved,
            it is promoted to the Stable channel and becomes available to all Defra teams.
          </li>
        </ol>

        <p class="govuk-body">
          To propose a server for evaluation, contact the AICE team via
          Slack <a class="govuk-link" href="{{ aceSlackChannel }}">#ask-ace</a>.
          Include a link to the server's repository, a brief description of the use case,
          and any relevant security or licensing information.
        </p>

      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
{% endblock %}
